headline: TSN Q3 Deep Dive: Chicken Momentum Offsets Beef Headwinds as Tyson Navigates Tight Protein Markets
summary: Meat company Tyson Foods (NYSE:TSN) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025 as sales rose 2.2% year on year to $13.86 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.15 per share was 37.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
